<TITLE> Mob kills 3 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, April 16 (bdnews24.com)  A mob beat three to persons to death in Boalkhali of Chittagong suspecting them of being bandits. Abdul Malek, officer in charge of the Boalkhali Police Station said that the incident took place in the early hours of Friday in Koibortiapara of Kodurkhali union. "Locals chased six young men suspecting them to be bandits. They managed to catch three of the youths and beat them severely," said Malik. Police said that the three died on the spot. Locals have said that the gang went to the area for committing robbery. They added that 700 to 800 villagers chased the youths after guards alarmed them. The police recovered one knife from the spot and sent the bodies to Chittagong Medical College Hospital for post-mortem. bdne
